article.headline: IPFW 76, UMKC 71
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Ben Botts scored 22 points, including two free throws to seal the win, as IPFW beat UMKC 76-71 Thursday night in the Summit League. Nick Daniels had 16, David Carson 15 and Dellvez Yearby 12 for the Mastodons (12-16, 7-10). Bakari Lewis scored 17 points to pace the Kangaroos (7-23, 3-14). Dustin Dibble had 15, Latreze Mushatt 14 and Tre McKinney-Jones 11. The Kangaroos opened with six unanswered points, but IPFW fought back to an 11-11 tie and the game remained nip and tuck en route to a 37-37 tie at halftime. UMKC opened the second half with a 6-0 run but Carson hit a layup to tie it at 47 with 11:34 left. Shortly after that, IPFW took control and led by as many as seven with 6:14 left. UMKC closed to within three with seven seconds left before Botts closed it out with his free throws.
